Fullstack Founder Factory Website & Application Code Repository

How to get this repo working:

1- Download this repo to your computer at the Home directory ('~/' on Mac or C:/Windows/Users/[your-name]/ on Windows).
2- You need 'Java 8' (http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html), 'mySQL' (https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/), and 'sbt' (http://www.scala-sbt.org/download.html) installed on your computer. Download and install them from the links provided if you don't have them.
3- You need to install bower (https://bower.io/).
4- You need to run 'bower install' in your terminal / command prompt to download some necessary javascript libraries.
5- You need to create a new database in mySQL called "fullstackcoding".
6- You need to run "./activator" in your terminal on Mac or "sbt" in your command prompt on Windows. Wait for it to work.
7- Then type "compile" and wait for it to finish compiling.
8- Then type "run" and it will tell you it's listening to port 9000, which means you should open a browser and go to http://localhost:9000.

Reach out with any questions.
